name: Canfield, Appellant, v. Baltimore & Ohio Railroad Company

judges: Before Mitchell, C. J., Dean, Fell, Mestbezat and Thompson, JJ.
parties: Canfield, Appellant, v. Baltimore & Ohio Railroad Company.

opinions.text:
Opinion by
Mr. Justice Thompson,
For the reasons given in Thomas J. Canfield v. The Baltimore & Ohio Railroad Company, No. 277, of January term, 1903, the assignment of error in this case is not sustained and the judgment is affirmed.
opinions.author: Mr. Justice Thompson,

casebody.head_matter:
Canfield, Appellant, v. Baltimore & Ohio Railroad Company.
Argued Feb. 11, 1904.
Appeal, No. 276, Jan. T., 1903, by plaintiff, from order of C. P. Delaware Co., Dec. T., 1903, No. 47, refusing to take off nonsuit in case of Thomas J. Can-field and Bridget Canfield, his Wife, v. The Baltimore & Ohio Railroad Company.
Before Mitchell, C. J., Dean, Fell, Mestbezat and Thompson, JJ.
Affirmed.
March 7, 1904:
